AGI - The EU has approved the 16th package of sanctions to be applied to Russia because of the invasion of Ukraine that has triggered a conflict that has lasted for 3 years. "The EU keeps promises: Foreign Ministers have just approved the 16th package of sanctions against Russia. It covers everything, from the ships of the shadow fleet to the game controllers used to control drones.> Now we have the most extensive sanctions ever, which weaken Russia's war effort." To write it, on X, to the High Representative of the EU for Foreign Affairs, Kaja Kallas, upon his arrival to the Foreign Council. Kallas also stressed that "at this moment more than ever" is important "supporting Ukraine".
<div </div
Responding to journalists, Kallas also intervened on the latest statements, unflattering, of Trump on Zelensky. "When I heard about Zelensky dictator, I was sure he was making a mistake and confuse the two people, because Putin did not have elections or Russia had no elections for 25 years >. Zelensky is the leader elected in free and fair elections. And of course, in time of war, you cannot have elections. Many countries have points in their constitutions that cannot be held elections. Why? Because in the elections we always meet inside, not in a situation where we actually have an external enemy, on which we must concentrate our forces". And again: "If you look at the messages that come from the United States, it is clear that the Russian narrative is very strongly represented," he added.&nbsp;
<h2> Metsola and von der Leyen</h2>
Kallas was not the only one to speak these days of 'anniversary' of the military operation triggered by Moscow against Kiev. "Three years of inspiration, resistance and probability challenge," wrote on X the President of the European Parliament, Roberta Metsola. Ursula von der Leyen also returned to the question by speaking directly from Kiev: "It is not only Ukraine's destiny to be at stake. It is the fate of Europe. So our first priority remains to strengthen the resistance of Ukraine. So far, our Union and the Member States have supported Ukraine with a figure of 134 billion euros. More than anyone."&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"Thanks to our Instrument for Ukraine and the G7 loan, we have filled Ukraine's budget gap for the entire year 2025. At the same time, we must accelerate the immediate delivery of weapons and ammunition. And this will be the center of our work in the coming weeks," he added. "Europe - it has concluded - is here to strengthen Ukraine at this critical moment. I can announce that a new payment of 3.5 billion euros for Ukraine will arrive in March >". &nbsp;
